article.description: Garrett Houser pulled in a 75-yard pass from George Martin for the winning touchdown in the fourth quarter as Robert Morris came from behind to defeat Bryant 24-20 Saturday to remain undefeated in the Northeast Conference.
article.headline: Robert Morris edged Bryant 24-20, comes from 13 points down
article.linkText: Robert Morris edged Bryant 24-20, comes from 13 points down
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Garrett Houser pulled in a 75-yard pass from George Martin for the winning touchdown in the fourth quarter as Robert Morris came from behind to defeat Bryant 24-20 Saturday to remain undefeated in the Northeast Conference. The Colonials (4-4, 3-0) fell behind 13-0 by halftime, their largest deficit since trailing Sacred Heart by 14 in 2010 -- also a comeback win. The Colonials outscored the Bulldogs (2-7, 1-3) 24-7 in the final two periods despite being outgained in rushing and passing yards. Back-to-back Bryant turnovers turned into 10 points. Brady Ours intercepted Bryant's Kory Curtis, leading to a Nick Bisceglia 29-yard field goal as the Colonials cut the gap to 13-10. The Bulldogs' Gavin Rowley was pushed back for a 16-yard loss on the next possession and fumbled. Jacob Thomas snatched it up at the 3 and scored for a 17-13 Colonials lead. Bryant took a 20-17 lead early in the fourth on Harrison Easton's 5-yard TD run, but Robert Morris responded with a three-play, 74-yard drive and the winning TD pass Jesse Nemerowicz, with six tackles, grabbed the career record for Bryant with 289. The previous record was 285.
